definition:
'the king' or a name, Hammelech in KJV of Jer.36.26; 38.6- a man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at Jer.36.26; 
 father of: Jerahmeel (H3396I) and Malchijah (H4441H); also translated "the king"; 
